    public interface FactoryProducer
    This class defines a way by which factories can be returned for the scope specified.

    2016-08-05
    Author:
    Tony Field

    • Method Detail

      • getFactory

        Factory getFactory(Object scope)
        Get the factory configured for the scope specified. If no factory is present for the specified scope, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        scope - the scope
        Returns:
        the factory
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if no factory exists for the specified scope. null is not a valid scope.
